               <head>Javahir-i shahi</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Javāhir-i shāhī by Jawhar Aftābah'chī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n50034146 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115921" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3946-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656322.0x000001 viaf_11698784">Jawhar
                           Aftābah'chī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656322.0x000001 viaf_11698784" type="alt">جوهر آفتابه
                           چى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_6746">Javāhir-i shāhī<add/>
                     </title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_6746">جواهر شاهى</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Alternative title stated in colophon: Tārīkh-i Humāyūnī <addName/>
                        </p>
                        <p>Official <term xml:lang="en">chronicle</term> of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656310.0x000001 viaf_11090963" role="subject">Humāyūn
                              Pādshāh</persName> by his ewer-bearer, by order of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_3264079" role="pat">Akbar
                              Pādshāh</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>Version differs from other standard editions with parts attributed to
                              <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_33145375892383680812" role="att">Ilāhdād Fayz̤ī</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>According to <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_22180382" role="cataloguer">Storey</persName>, "one would be disposed to regard
                           this MS. as representing Jauhar's original draft, rather than a
                           recension." 
                        </p>
                        <p>Although the colophon dates the volume to the mid seventeenth century,
                           this is likely to be a later copy (circa early eighteenth century) with
                           the original colophon reproduced verbatim</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Transcribed by order of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7663" role="fmo">G. J. Nicholls</persName>, Judge at <name type="place">Farrukhabad</name>, from a manuscript obtained from <name type="place">Agra</name>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
